properties.abstract: From the marriage of the Aare and Rhine through flat Wehntal to Zurich, then the oasis of the Neeracher Riet reed beds, exposed to aeronautic noise, soon the Tss, extensive fields, just touching Winterthur, on over the Seercken to the silvery Untersee.
properties.description:
A union of waters, the confluence of the Aare and Rhine, the Klingnauer reservoir warms Dttingen grapes and the striking synagogue is an eye-catcher in Endingen. In flat, once rural Wehntal, the bustle of Zurichs outer areas slowly makes itself felt.

Within hearing distance of the airport, the route crosses the Neeracher Riet, a shrinking marshland with spotted crakes and highland cattle in moor grass. In Blach the 340-year-old Rathaus (town hall) with its splendid timber-framed faade makes an impression. Over the Dttenberg down to the Tss, along flat fields and through suburbs. The route just touches the northern edge of Winterthur, but not without making a short detour to the Technorama.

Then on through the middle of Frauenfeld, Thurgaus main city, and over the Thur to Pfyn, where the Romans passed through and people lived in pile dwellings, most recently in the 2007 Swiss TV series. With quite a few drops of sweat up over the remote Seercken, then a flicker of light, the attractive Untersee invites you to Steckbornein.
properties.title: Studenland-Tss-Rmer-Route
